I bought this a while ago for a woods gun. I fired it for the first time yesterday and it's a nice accurate shooter. Manufactured in 1979. It has a few scratches and the bottom of the grips show some wear. However, it doesn't seem to actually been fired much at all, although there's a turn ring on the cylinder. There's zero flame burn on the top of the frame. There's a light scratch behind the recoil shield on the left side and three tiny dings on the right front of the barrel. I tried to show the imperfections in the pics. The marks aren't all that noticeable. The pics also make the flaws look worse than they are.
